Min.js")

1. Serialize : serializes an object to string (depends on type xml/json/jsv/base64/...) 2. Deserialize : deserializes a string to object (depends on type xml/json/jsv/base64/...) 3. DeepCopy : performs deep copied an object

FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Fixed bug in the WindowNavigationService, which caused the view models to not be deactivated when the user clicked the closing button of the window.

FeedPackage.Description: The MVVM Framework is a compact and simple, yet powerful implementation of the MVVM pattern. It provides a strong model for managing the application lifecycle and the navigation. The MVVM framework decouples operation system functionality from the application logic by providing a powerful service system, which abstracts away any platform specific code from the application logic. Everything in the framework was build with the task awaitable pattern in mind, from application lifecycle management to navigation. The framework plays nice with all kinds of frameworks, for example the dependency injection mechanism build into the framework does not care what
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: The project was largely restructured and the strong ties to Ninject were removed.

FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Fixed a problem in the enum display name value converter. If the resource existed, but was empty, then not an empty string, but the name of the enum value was returned. Also added a custom boolean to visibility value converter, which, unlike the standard boolean to visibility converter, does not return DependencyProperty.UnsetValue, when the input value is null, but it returns Visibility.Collapsed. This is very helpful, when the binding is asynchronous, because in an asynchronous binding, the value can be undetermined (i.e. null) for a short amount of time, which results in the control to be displayed for a short period of time, even if the binding value eventually evaluates to false.
